CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 15, 1962, pg. 2, reads: "Thinkers - Among guests at Sunday's 'Operation Think' meeting at Westray Plaza were, left to right, standing: An unidentified guardsman, James Aanford, Luther Sewell, Harold Keith, Bill Carter, John Sinclair, Wendell Freeland and W.P. Young. Seated at table: Mrs. Minona Clinton, Councilman James A. Jordon, Johnny Wheeler and Bill Paige.  Seated below the platform are Harold McClain, Cal Spittler, Charles E. Pendleton, James Edmonds, Ed Bryant, Ernest O'Connor Jr., Curtis Hefflin, Thurston (Ducky) Lane, Robert Ficklin and Oscar Buckner. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Audience of women and men, seated facing stage in Westray Plaza for Operation Think meeting
